<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Portfolio Report</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; background: #0e1117; color: #e0e0e0; margin: 0; padding: 20px; }
        h1, h2, h3 { color: #fff; }
        .container { max-width: 1400px; margin: 0 auto; }
        .section { background: #1e1e1e; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 8px; }
        .grid-2 { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; }
        table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-bottom: 15px; }
        th, td { text-align: left; padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #333; }
        th { background: #2a2a2a; color: #fff; }
        .alert-warning { background-color: #332b00; border-left: 4px solid #cc9900; padding: 15px; margin: 15px 0; }
        a { color: #4CAF50; text-decoration: none; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
    <h1>Portfolio Analysis Report</h1>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>1. Portfolio Composition</h2>
        <p>Strategies included: {{ meta.strategies | join(', ') }}</p>
        <p>Sizing method: {{ meta.sizing_method }}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section grid-2">
        <div>
            <h2>2. Headline Metrics (Equal Weight)</h2>
            {{ sections.s2_headline | safe }}
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2>3. Capital Efficiency</h2>
            {{ sections.s3_capital | safe }}
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>4. Combined Equity Curve</h2>
        {{ sections.s4_equity | safe }}
    </div>

    <div class="section grid-2">
        <div>
            <h2>5. Correlation Matrix (Pearson)</h2>
            {{ sections.s5_corr_pearson | safe }}
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2>6. Rolling 60-day Correlation</h2>
            {{ sections.s6_corr_rolling | safe }}
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>7. Drawdown Attribution</h2>
        {{ sections.s7_dd | safe }}
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>8. Position Sizing Comparison</h2>
        {{ sections.s8_sizing_table | safe }}
        {{ sections.s8_sizing_chart | safe }}
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>9. Kelly Reference</h2>
        <div class="alert-warning">
            <strong>Mentor Disclaimer:</strong> Kelly fractions are shown for reference only. This project sizes positions via volatility targeting. Kelly assumes the historical distribution of returns will repeat; real markets violate this assumption and Kelly sizing has destroyed real traders using real strategies that looked real on paper.
        </div>
        {{ sections.s9_kelly | safe }}
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>10. Data Dictionary</h2>
        <p>Refer to the <a href="data_dictionary.html" target="_blank">Portfolio Data Dictionary</a> for term definitions.</p>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
